    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Exhaust Back Pressure (EBP) Sensor</title>
        <figure id="f2650211010" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK09/K09040.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>EBP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>The EBP sensor, a variable capacitance sensor, measures exhaust back pressure before the turbochargers.
        </para>
        <para>The EBP sensor provides feedback to the ECM for closed loop control of the turbocharger Boost Control
            Solenoid (BCS), EGR rate calculations, and Intake Throttle Valve (ITV) control.
        </para>
        <para>The EBP sensor is installed in a tube connected to the left exhaust manifold.</para>
    </svcproc>
